# webnet_app Project Rules

## Dependency Isolation

- **Always use local dependencies** from `node_modules`. Never rely on globally installed packages.
- Run `npm install` from the project directory to ensure all dependencies are available locally.
- Use `npm run clean-install` when you need a fresh environment (removes node_modules and package-lock.json, then reinstalls).

## Repository root (μία ρίζα)

- Το **root** του project είναι ο φάκελος που περιέχει αυτό το `package.json` με dependency **`expo`**.
- Τρέχεις **πάντα** από εδώ: `npm install`, `npx expo start`, `npx expo prebuild`, `npm run ios` — **όχι** από γονικό φάκελο (`.../cursor/` κ.λπ.).
- Αν βλέπεις δύο εμφωλευμένους φακέλους `webnet_app`, κράτα μόνο αυτόν που έχει `expo` στο `package.json`.

## Project Structure

Ακολούθησε τη δομή φακέλων (ρίζα repo):

```
./
├── src/
│   ├── api/          # Firebase config, types, API calls
│   ├── components/   # Reusable UI components (Cards, Buttons)
│   ├── context/      # AuthContext, GlobalState
│   ├── hooks/        # Custom hooks (useSearch, useFriends)
│   ├── navigation/   # AuthStack, MainStack, navigators
│   └── screens/      # Auth, User, Professional, Admin screens
├── App.tsx
├── global.css
└── ...
```

- Place new API logic in `src/api/`
- Place reusable UI in `src/components/`
- Place screens in `src/screens/` under Auth, User, Professional, or Admin
- Place navigation in `src/navigation/`
- Place context providers in `src/context/`
- Place custom hooks in `src/hooks/`

## Node Version

- Use the Node version specified in `.nvmrc` (run `nvm use` before working).
- Do not assume a different Node version.
